\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.2}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Left:} Adjunction structure $\setbox \z@ \hbox {\mathsurround \z@ $\textstyle F$}\mathaccent "0365{F} \dashv G$ with unit $\eta = G \circ \setbox \z@ \hbox {\mathsurround \z@ $\textstyle F$}\mathaccent "0365{F}$. \textbf  {Right:} The triangle $G \circ \setbox \z@ \hbox {\mathsurround \z@ $\textstyle F$}\mathaccent "0365{F} \neq  \mathrm  {id}_\mathcal  {X}$ fails generically; this failure is the categorical formulation of irreversibility. When $\setbox \z@ \hbox {\mathsurround \z@ $\textstyle F$}\mathaccent "0365{F}$ is non-injective, no right inverse $G$ can make the outer triangle commute for all $X \in \mathcal  {X}$.}}{20}{figure.5.2}\protected@file@percent }
